description.narrative: Government and partners have enhanced capacity to deliver quality education for improved learning outcomes for children in elementary education, which contributes to Learning Outcomes, Learning Outcomes (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Business and Key Business Stakeholders demonstrate growing willingness, commitment and resource allocation for protecting and promoting child rights in policy and practice by 2022

description.narrative: Capacity of national and state level education functionaries enhanced in designing and implementation of robust and responsive large-scale and school-based assessments; for demonstration and scale up of child- centered teaching learning practices ; and local learning hubs such as block and cluster resource centres equipped to provide on-site supportive supervision and academic leadership to deliver equitable quality education and improving learning outcomes of children. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:13/01/2020
